properties.name: hybrid
properties.description: Indicates whether the application is a combination of Angular and AngularJS.
properties.rawdescription: Indicates whether the application is a combination of Angular and AngularJS.

properties.name: rootNavigatorNode
properties.description: The root node of the navigator, which can be either a NavigatorNode or NavigatorNodeData. This serves as the entry point for navigation structure for Alarms views.
properties.rawdescription:
The root node of the navigator, which can be either a `NavigatorNode` or `NavigatorNodeData`.

properties.name: route
properties.description: An array of Route objects representing the navigation routes available. Each route defines a navigation path and its associated components related to Alarms.
properties.rawdescription:
An array of `Route` objects representing the navigation routes available.
